oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Electric tower at Hales Bar Dam
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of people standing on an electric tower at Hales Bar Dam.

Hales Bar Dam was a hydroelectric dam located along the Tennessee River at just over 431 miles, near the southwest end of the Tennessee River Gorge. The dam's reservoir extended up the river through the gorge all the way to Chattanooga, and had 162 miles of shoreline. Construction of the dam began in 1905, began operation on November 13, 1913 and closed on December 14, 1967.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
